### Gum Installation: Fedora/RHEL/OpenSuse (YUM/DNF/Zypper)

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/gum/blob/main/README.md

Installs Gum on Fedora, RHEL, or OpenSuse systems using their respective package managers (yum, dnf, or zypper). This process involves adding a repository configuration file.

```bash
echo '[charm]
name=Charm
baseurl=https://repo.charm.sh/yum/
enabled=1
gpgcheck=1
gpgkey=https://repo.charm.sh/yum/gpg.key' | sudo tee /etc/yum.repos.d/charm.repo
sudo rpm --import https://repo.charm.sh/yum/gpg.key

# For yum/dnf
sudo yum install gum

# For zypper
sudo zypper refresh
sudo zypper install gum
```

