### Combine Text Vertically and Horizontally with Gum Join

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/gum/blob/main/README.md

The `gum join` command combines text outputs either vertically or horizontally. It's often used with `gum style` to create visually appealing layouts. Ensure that the output of `gum style` is quoted when used as an argument to `gum join` to preserve newline characters.

```bash
I=$(gum style --padding "1 5" --border double --border-foreground 212 "I")
LOVE=$(gum style --padding "1 4" --border double --border-foreground 57 "LOVE")
BUBBLE=$(gum style --padding "1 8" --border double --border-foreground 255 "Bubble")
GUM=$(gum style --padding "1 5" --border double --border-foreground 240 "Gum")

I_LOVE=$(gum join "$I" "$LOVE")
BUBBLE_GUM=$(gum join "$BUBBLE" "$GUM")
gum join --align center --vertical "$I_LOVE" "$BUBBLE_GUM"
```

